cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.AR, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the design of 5G mobile edge computing networks and their communication links. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of error-correcting codes to combat channel blocking and improve communication reliability. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is a possibility as the paper mentions the use of millimeter-wave radio signals, which are relevant to hardware design. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possibility as the paper discusses methods to optimize power and latency in offloading computational tasks to MEC servers. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possibility as the paper discusses the use of edge cloud computing to run applications on user devices' behalf.
